# 86-vibe Workspace Layout

This workspace has three roots. Each has a single primary responsibility per AEP-001-08.

| Repository | Role | Write code here? |
|------------|------|------------------|
| **86-vibe-platform** | Architecture (ARP/AEP/IWP), standards, templates, governance | No — specs and docs only |
| **86-vibe-cli** | Platform CLI implementation (`86vibe` command) | Yes — all platform service and CLI code |
| **86-vibe-example** | Reference implementation and regression validation | Yes — example projects and validation only |

## Dependency direction

```text
86-vibe-platform
        ├──────────────┐
        ▼              ▼
86-vibe-cli     86-vibe-example
        └──────────────┘
              ▼
      86-vibe-example
```

- Platform SHALL NOT depend on CLI or Example.
- CLI MAY depend on Platform.
- Example MAY depend on Platform and CLI.
- Do not introduce circular dependencies.

## Task routing

| Task type | Read from | Implement in |
|-----------|-----------|--------------|
| IWP or service implementation | `86-vibe-platform/architecture/` | `86-vibe-cli/src/vibe/` |
| Architecture or standards change | `86-vibe-platform/` | `86-vibe-platform/` only |
| Reference example or release validation | `86-vibe-platform/architecture/` | `86-vibe-example/` |
| Regression tests for platform releases | Platform + CLI specs | `86-vibe-example/tests/` |

## IWP → CLI package mapping

| Service / area | Path in 86-vibe-cli |
|----------------|---------------------|
| CLI commands | `src/vibe/cli/` |
| Configuration Service | `src/vibe/configuration/` |
| Logging Service | `src/vibe/logging/` |
| Bootstrap | `src/vibe/bootstrap/` |
| Version metadata | `src/vibe/version.py` |

When an IWP names `Implementation Repository: 86-vibe-cli`, all code and tests go in **86-vibe-cli**, not in the platform or example repos.
